						               													<description>Quest Crawler is a solitaire game that allow player to travel fantasy land, performing quests, fighting creatures and malicious bosses and strength party of brave heroes to fulfil final quest - to defeat the Dragon of Death.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game is free to download, print and play. Game require D8 dice. Game can be played during journey due to minimal space and resource requirements also can be paused and restored at any moment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay is based on turns which are divided into separate phases:&amp;#10;- Quest generation phase if party isn't on quest - with use of random quest generator&amp;#10;- Movement phase allowing player to move his party across land from region to region from zone to zone&amp;#10;- Combat phase if quest or encounter test brings enemy - combat divide in combat rounds when all actions take place simultaneously&amp;#10;- Quest resolve phase - returning quests, delivering items (some quests ends by themselves during other phases)&amp;#10;- Party manage phase - when in city player can buy levels and learn abilities, sell or enchant items&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What QC have:&amp;#10;- party of 3 heroes (choose from 9 different characters, each described with HESDIAR parameters)&amp;#10;- experience, levelling, abilities and talents system&amp;#10;- land contains 4 zones to travel and  of hostile creatures to fight with&amp;#10;- dungeons in each zone with more powerful bosses&amp;#10;- randomly generated quests of 5 types&amp;#10;- randomly generated loot (equipment)&amp;#10;- enchanting equipment&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What QC do not have:&amp;#10;- modular board&amp;#10;- cards&amp;#10;- complicated rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What QC really is:&amp;#10;- board roll'n'slash&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Check &amp;quot;Forum&amp;quot; section for downloadable files.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
